%N A387687 a(n) is the smallest prime p greater than all previous terms such that the product of the previous terms plus p is prime.
%C A387687 The presence of the even prime 2 makes this sequence work. a(0) = 2 since the empty product is 1 and 1 + 2 = 3 is a prime.
%e A387687 2 + 3 = 5 (a prime).
%e A387687 2 * 3 + 5 = 11 (a prime).
%e A387687 2 * 3 * 5 * 7 * 13 * 19 + 23 = 51893 (a prime).
%e A387687 2 * 3 * 5 * 7 * 13 * 19 * 23 * 31 * 41 * 61 + 67 = 92495258377 (a prime).
